1.Kill
  kill command is used to terminate or send signals to running processes.

kill 5678

SIGTERM (default), -2 SIGINT (interrupt), -9  SIGKILL (immediate termination)

  2.pkill
  pkill command, you can specify the process name or a pattern that matches the process name.

  pkill -f firefox

3.Nohup
nohup command allows you to run a process that will continue to run even after you log out, preventing it from being terminated.

  nohup sleep 60 &
This will run the sleep 60 command in the background, and the output will be saved to a file named nohup.out in the current directory.
  The & at the end of the command runs the process in the background, and the output shows the process ID (PID) of the background process.
